We obtained the number of flu tweets from HealthTweets.org. The data collection process in HealthTweets.org uses “streams” of public data of Twitter. The “health” stream downloads only tweets containing any of the 269 health-related keywords, which include lists for possessive words, flu related words, fear related words, “self” words, and “other” words. The specific data collection methodology is explained in Lamb et al. (2013). Figure 6 plots the daily normalized number of flu tweets in the 2018–2019 season. These data will serve as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
