				\begin{document}$${R}_{0}$$\end{document}R0 increases (i.e., the disease becomes more contagious), the peak magnitude, the total infected, and the total deaths all increase sharply; but the peak time shortens, and the vaccine coverage decreases. For example, in a severe flu season (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
